cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 470 miles ESE of Key West, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: continuing west-northwest north of Cuba, forecast to pass near the Florida Keys Saturday, then move into the eastern Gulf and curve northwest toward the Florida Panhandle early Monday
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Panhandle (near the Big Bend / Apalachicola area)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Florida Keys west of Ocean Reef to the Dry Tortugas and the southwest coast of Florida from Bonita Beach south and east to Ocean Reef including Florida Bay; several central Cuban provinces
weather_observation.impacted_coast: North coast of Cuba, the Bahamas, Florida Keys and southern peninsula, eastern Gulf Coast, and Florida Panhandle to southeast Alabama/Georgia
weather_observation.wind: Tropical-storm-force winds are not expected; occasional gusts below gale force possible mid-week as remnants pass inland.
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along the Delaware coast from Fred.
weather_observation.rainfall: Periods of moderate to locally heavy rain possible 18â€“19 Aug as remnants move through the Mid-Atlantic, brief urban or small-stream flooding possible.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Up-river flooding on Delaware River could be aggravated if heavy upstream rainfall occurs; supply-chain delays likely from Gulf-coast impacts.
